[[File:Wahlkreis Epembe in Ohangwena.png|thumb|Location of Epembe constituency (yellow) in the Ohangwena Region (dark grey)]]
'''Epembe''' is a constituency in the [[Ohangwena Region]] of [[Namibia]], on the border to [[Angola]]. It has 14,837 inhabitants,<ref>[http://www.statoids.com/yna.html Constituencies of Namibia, 2004]</ref> the district centre is the settlement of [[Epembe]]. 

Villages in this constituency include Eenheni, Egongo, Ekuma, Etambo la Mushi Onamogani, Etapa, Iikelo, Ohenghono-Ohamikoka, Onhinda, Okuuya, Othilku, Oondunda, Onamvula A, Onamungonzi, Omuhongo, Omalambo, Onanyati, Ombaba, Oshamono, Okahwandada, Oshiweda, Onaame, Omushuwa, Omufiya wa Amutenya wa Shiweda, Ohamwiimbi, Okakwena, Onhinda, Ohamatundu Omevataahekele, Okamwandi, [[Onangolo]] and Onamundidi. Many of them are only accessible via [[4x4]], have only weak cell phone network coverage, and [[Water supply and sanitation in Namibia|access to clean water]] is not universally available. Health and education facilities are far away for many residents, with the nearest clinics at Epembe and Onangolo.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Waiting for the fruits of independence |last=Shivute |first=Oswald |newspaper=[[The Namibian]] |date=15 April 2016 |page=6 |url=http://www.namibian.com.na/Waiting-for-the-fruits-of-independence/39463 }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | title=Humans, animals compete for water at Epembe | last=Itamalo | first=Marx | newspaper=[[The Namibian]] | date=29 August 2016 | pages=6-7 | url=http://www.namibian.com.na/Humans-animals-compete-for-water-at-Epembe/44789/read}}</ref>

==Politics==
Namibia's ruling [[South West Africa People's Organization|SWAPO Party]] won the [[Namibian local and regional elections, 2015|2015 regional election]] uncontested, as no opposition party fielded a candidate.<ref name=uncontested>{{cite news|last=Kangootui |first=Nomhle |newspaper=[[The Namibian]] |title=Swapo gets ǃNamiǂNûs uncontested |url=http://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?page=read&id=33153 |date=23 October 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151024163513/http://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?page=read&id=33153 |archivedate=October 24, 2015 }}</ref>

