[[File:Kinshasa CENI Headquarter (6425184603).jpg|thumb|CENI Headquarters in Kinshasa]]
The '''Independent National Electoral Commission''' ('''{{lang-fr|Commission Électorale Nationale Indépendante}}''' or '''CENI''') is the body that runs elections in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
[[File:DRC-Ceni-Nico-230-NP.jpg|thumb|A CENI election official speaks to the [[Voice of America]]]]

This organization was tasked with executing the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo general election, 2016|country's 2016 general election]]. However, it delayed the election until 2018 "because the number of voters isn’t known."<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wilson|first1=Thomas|last2=Mbatha|first2=Amogelgang|title=Congo Election Body Proposes Two-Year Wait for Presidential Vote|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-09-29/congo-to-hold-elections-in-2018-at-earliest-electoral-body-says|accessdate=29 September 2016|work=[[Bloomberg BusinessWeek]]|date=29 September 2016|ref=Bloomberg}}</ref> The country's political opposition has alleged that [[President of the Democratic Republic of the Congo|the country's president]] [[Joseph Kabila]] is trying to remain in power after his [[Constitution of the Democratic Republic of the Congo|constitutionally]] mandated term expires.<ref name="BBC">{{cite news|title=DR Congo election: 17 dead in anti-Kabila protests|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-37406407|accessdate=29 September 2016|work=[[BBC News]]|agency=[[BBC]]|date=19 September 2016}}</ref> 

CENI's bank accounts are held at the [[BGFIBank Group]].<ref name="lemondejeanjacquesbanquier">{{cite news|last1=Mannier|first1=Xavier|title=Jean-Jacques Lumumba, banquier congolais exilé et dénonciateur du système Kabila|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/afrique/article/2016/12/22/jean-jacques-lumumba-banquier-congolais-exile-et-denonciateur-du-systeme-kabila_5053068_3212.html|accessdate=December 23, 2016|work=Le Monde|date=December 22, 2016|quote=
La BGFI est en effet une banque très politique qui héberge notamment les comptes de la Commission électorale nationale et indépendante (CENI). C’est cette institution qui, faute de moyens pour recenser l’électorat, a demandé au président de reporter l’élection présidentielle aux calendes grecques et fournit à la majorité présidentielle l’argumentaire pour que Joseph Kabila se maintienne au pouvoir après l’expiration de son mandat, ce 19 décembre.}}</ref> It held US$55 million as of May 2016.<ref name="lemondejeanjacquesbanquier"/> The same month, it borrowed an additional US$25 million from the BFGIBank,<ref name="lemondejeanjacquesbanquier"/> with $2.4 million in fees.<ref name="bloombergcongoelectionbodysaidto">{{cite news|last1=Kavanagh|first1=Michael|last2=Wild|first2=Franz|last3=Wilson|first3=Thomas|title=Congo Election Body Said to Pay Millions to Kabila-Tied Bank|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-11-01/congo-election-body-said-to-pay-millions-to-kabila-linked-bank|accessdate=December 23, 2016|work=Bloomberg|date=November 1, 2016}}</ref> According to ''[[Le Monde]]'', the 2016 presidential elections were postponed on the grounds that the CENI lacked sufficient funds to register voters.<ref name="lemondejeanjacquesbanquier"/>

CENI's president is Corneille Nangaa.<ref name="bloombergcongoelectionbodysaidto"/>

