'''Krokodil Festival''' (''Knjzevno Regionalno Okupljanje Koje Otklanja Dosadu I Letargiju'') is a [[literary festival]], with the main event held annually in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]]. The festival mostly presents authors from the region of former [[Yugoslavia]] ([[Croatia]], [[Bosnia and Hercegovina]], [[Slovenia]], [[Montenegro]] and Serbia) with exceptions like authors from [[Germany]] or [[Denmark]].{{fact|date=August 2014}} The main festival event is the ''Belgrade Summer Krokodil'', a three-day or two-day festival held in June.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://english.traduki.eu/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1685:sechstes-literaturfestival-krokodil-in-belgrad&catid=292&Itemid=148 | title=6th Literary Festival KROKODIL in Belgrade | publisher=[http://english.traduki.eu/ Traduki] | date=July 2014 | accessdate=4 August 2014 }}</ref>
==Overview== The festival was founded in 2009. Since then there were eight main festival events held in Belgrade and several one-day festivals in [[Pula]] (Croatia), [[Ljubljana]] (Slovenia), [[Leipzig]] (Germany) and [[Inđija]] (Serbia) – as part of the "Krokodil – On the Road" programme.{{fact|date=August 2014}}
Festival events have been held in the locality of the [[Museum of Yugoslav History]].{{fact|date=August 2014}}
The festival is directed by [[Vladimir Arsenijević]] and Ana Pejović.{{fact|date=August 2014}}
