'''Marienfeld Abbey''' is a [[Cistercian]] nunnery in Marienfeld, [[Wullersdorf]], eight kilometres north of [[Hollabrunn]]. It was founded by [[Hans Hermann Groër]] as a sister house of [[Mariastern Abbey, Hohenweiler|Mariastern Abbey]]. Its construction began in 1974 and it was opened on 14 November 1982 by [[Franz König]], then [[Archbishop of Vienna]].

