{{Politics of Benin}}

The '''Scout Alliance''' ({{lang-fr|Alliance Eclaireur}}) is a [[political alliance]] in [[Benin]] led by [[Edmond Agoua]].

==History==
The alliance was launched on 20 February 2015.<ref>[http://www.lanationbenin.info/index.php/k2/item/452-actualite-politique-l-alliance-eclaireur-veut-faire-souffler-un-autre-vent-sur-le-benin Political news: Scout alliance wants another wind to blow in Benin] La Nation, 23 February 2015</ref> It included the [[Party for Democracy and Social Progress]], the [[Renewal Party for Solidarity and Progress]],  the [[Coalition for an Emerging Benin]], the [[Common Action Front for the Emergence of a New Ethic in Benin]], the [[New Alliance for Development]], the [[Party for the Impulse of Development and Active Solidarity]], the [[Movement for Social Democracy (Benin)|Movement for Social Democracy]], the [[Party of Collective Awakening for a Better Tomorrow]], the [[Wadedji Democratic Party]], the [[Liberal Reformer Party]], [[Generation-Action-Progress]], the [[Young Turks (Benin)|Young Turks]], the [[Movement for Solidarity and Durable Development]] and the [[Youth Movement for the Emergence of Couffo]].<ref>[http://www.lapressedujour.net/archives/39394 Echiquier politique : L’alliance « Eclaireur » portée sur les fonts baptismaux] La Press du Jour, 23 February 2015</ref>

The alliance won two seats in the [[Beninese parliamentary election, 2015|2015 parliamentary elections]].<ref>[http://www.cour-constitutionnelle-benin.org/dminutes/cmunike6.pdf Proclamation of the results of the legislative elections of 26 April 2015] Constitutional Court</ref>

